                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Design/development of solutions</span>Graduates will be able to develop sustainable solutions for complex engineering problems which fulfill the specified demand along with the consideration of public health and safety, societal and environmental considerations.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Conduct investigations of complex problems</span>Graduates will be able to investigate the complex problems using their research based knowledge and will be able to design experiments, analyze and interpret data and syntheses the information to get valid results.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Modern tools/techniques usage</span>Graduates will be able to identify appropriate resources, tools and techniques with an understanding of limitations for the prediction and modeling of complex engineering problems. </div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">The engineer and society</span>Graduates will be able to fulfill the responsibility relevant to professional engineering practices by applying their reasoning to solve societal, health, safety, legal and cultural issues.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Environment, sustainability and Ethics</span>Graduates will be able to understand the impact of professional engineering solutions on the society and environment and will develop sustainable solutions along with the professional ethics and responsibilities.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Individual and team work</span>Graduates will be able to communicate effectively with engineering community and will be able to write and design documents/presentations efficiently both as an individual and as a member or leader in a diverse team.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px ;font-weight:700;">Project management and finance</span>Graduates will be able to demonstrate knowledge and apply engineering and management principles to their own work or while managing outside projects.</div>
                                                </li>
                                               
                                                
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                       
                                    </div>
                                    <!-- Program Outcome Ends -->
                                    
                                    <!-- Program Specific Outcome Starts -->
                                    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                        <div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr" style="padding-bottom: 20px ;">
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap clearfix">
                                                <h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 22px ;font-weight: 600 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;text-transform: none ;color: #223d71 ;margin-right: 30px ;">PROGRAM SPECIFIC OUTCOMES</h3>
                                                <div class="gdlr-core-title-item-divider gdlr-core-right gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="font-size: 22px ;border-bottom-width: 3px ;"></div>
                                            </div>
                                          </div> 
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix " style="padding-bottom: 25px ;">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px;font-weight:700;">Program Specific Outcome 1</span>Civil Engineering graduates will have the requisite understanding and possess the ability to plan, design, construct and maintain engineering facilities in tandem with global, economic and societal contexts.</div>
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=" gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="margin-bottom: 18px ;"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon-wrap" style="margin-top: 5px ;"><i class="gdlr-core-icon-list-icon fa fa-dot-circle-o" style="color: #3db166 ;font-size: 18px ;width: 18px ;" ></i></span>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content-wrap"><span class="gdlr-core-icon-list-content" style="font-size: 18px;font-weight:700;">Program Specific Outcome 2</span>Graduates will hold leadership responsibilities in Civil Engineering Organizations and/or establish their own enterprises and interact to work seamlessly, independently and/or in multi-disciplinary teams.</div>
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                        
                                    </div>
                                    <!-- Program Specific Outcome Ends -->
                                    
                                    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                        <div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr" style="padding-bottom: 20px ;">
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap clearfix">
                                                <h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 22px ;font-weight: 600 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;text-transform: none ;color: #223d71 ;margin-right: 30px ;">Career Opportunities</h3>
                                                <div class="gdlr-core-title-item-divider gdlr-core-right gdlr-core-skin-divider" style="font-size: 22px ;border-bottom-width: 3px ;"></div>
                                                <p style="margin-top:10px;">Civil Engineering is considered as one of the oldest branches of engineering. Civil Engineers happen to be the central figures in building the infrastructure of a nation. Civil engineers will always remain in demand as development of infrastructure, i.e., construction of buildings, skyscrapers, roads, highways, dams, bridges, water treatment plants, sewage treatment plants, etc. to name a few, rely on their expertise and talent. It is an enormous field which provides infinite opportunities to work with Government/Public and Private sectors. It has an additional aspect where Civil Engineers can become an entrepreneurs or start consultancy firms. After completing B.Tech / M.Tech in Civil Engineering, students have ample career opportunites in higher studies and jobs as mentioned below.</p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                        
                                    </div>
                                    
                                    
